---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Contact — uxward">
  <style>
    .top { padding: var(--space-8) 0 var(--space-7); }
    .top a.back {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .top a.back:hover { color: var(--ink); }

    .name-block { padding: var(--space-8) 0 var(--space-9); }
    .name-eyebrow {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
    }
    h1.name {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: clamp(48px, 6vw, 88px);
      line-height: 1.0;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 30;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin: 0;
      max-width: 1080px;
    }
    h1.name em {
      font-style: italic; font-weight: 400;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 100, 'WONK' 1;
    }
    .deck {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-style: italic;
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: var(--body);
      margin: var(--space-7) 0 0;
      max-width: 660px;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 36, 'SOFT' 80, 'WONK' 1;
    }

    .bleed {
      background: var(--signature);
      color: #FFFFFF;
      padding: 128px 0 120px;
      margin-top: var(--space-9);
    }
    .bleed .eyebrow {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    }
    .bleed h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: clamp(48px, 6.4vw, 88px);
      line-height: 1.02;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      color: #FFFFFF;
      margin: 0;
      max-width: 980px;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 30;
    }
    .bleed h2 em {
      font-style: italic; font-weight: 400;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 100, 'WONK' 1;
    }
    .bleed a.email {
      margin-top: var(--space-9);
      display: inline-block;
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: clamp(28px, 3.4vw, 44px);
      line-height: 1.1;
      letter-spacing: -0.015em;
      color: #FFFFFF;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
      text-underline-offset: 8px;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 30;
    }
    .bleed a.email:hover { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.82); }
    .bleed .kicker {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
      margin-top: var(--space-5);
    }

    .section {
      padding: var(--space-10) 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .section-eyebrow {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    }
    .section-head {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: 36px;
      line-height: 1.1;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin: 0 0 var(--space-8) 0;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 30;
      max-width: 720px;
    }
    .section-head em {
      font-style: italic; font-weight: 400;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 100, 'WONK' 1;
    }

    .channels { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
    .channel-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 200px;
      gap: var(--space-7);
      padding: var(--space-5) 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
      align-items: baseline;
    }
    .channel-row .where {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
    }
    .channel-row .what {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 17px;
      line-height: 1.55;
      color: var(--body);
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24, 'SOFT' 80, 'WONK' 1;
    }
    .channel-row a.go {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 17px;
      color: var(--ink);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 4px;
      text-align: right;
    }
    .channel-row a.go:hover { color: var(--tertiary); }

    .faq { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
    .faq-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-8);
      padding: var(--space-7) 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
      align-items: baseline;
    }
    .faq-row .q {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-weight: 500;
      font-size: 19px;
      line-height: 1.3;
      color: var(--ink);
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 36, 'SOFT' 30;
    }
    .faq-row .a {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 17.5px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: var(--body);
      max-width: 580px;
    }
    .faq-row .a em { font-style: italic; }

    .note p {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 17px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: var(--body);
      max-width: 580px;
      margin: 0;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24, 'SOFT' 80, 'WONK' 1;
    }
    .note .stamp {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
      margin-top: var(--space-6);
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .channel-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .channel-row a.go { text-align: left; }
      .faq-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="container top">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="marker">§ ↩</div>
      <div><a class="back" href="/">— Back home</a></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container name-block">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="marker">§ 00</div>
      <div>
        <div class="name-eyebrow">— Contact —</div>
        <h1 class="name">The <em>direct line</em>, and a few notes on using it.</h1>
        <p class="deck">
          Most of what's here applies to recruiters, hiring managers, and reporters. If you're
          a friend of the work and want to write — even briefer than a cold email is fine.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="bleed">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="marker" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);">§ 01</div>
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">— Currently considering —</div>
          <h2>Senior design leadership roles. <em>Direct line below.</em></h2>
          <a class="email" href="mailto:brandon@uxward.com">brandon@uxward.com</a>
          <div class="kicker">— Read daily · Reply within two business days —</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="marker">§ 02</div>
        <div>
          <div class="section-eyebrow">— Other channels —</div>
          <h3 class="section-head">Email is the right one. <em>The rest are listed for completeness.</em></h3>
          <div class="channels">
            <div class="channel-row">
              <span class="where">— LinkedIn —</span>
              <span class="what">Same record, longer form. Connection requests welcome.</span>
              <a class="go" href="https://linkedin.com/in/brandonebward" target="_blank" rel="noopener">/in/brandonebward →</a>
            </div>
            <div class="channel-row">
              <span class="where">— GitHub —</span>
              <span class="what">FORGE, RAD, the Markdown plugin, a few smaller artifacts.</span>
              <a class="go" href="https://github.com/brandonebward" target="_blank" rel="noopener">/brandonebward →</a>
            </div>
            <div class="channel-row">
              <span class="where">— Calendar —</span>
              <span class="what">By introduction only. Email first, scheduling link after.</span>
              <a class="go" href="mailto:brandon@uxward.com">— By email —</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="marker">§ 03</div>
        <div>
          <div class="section-eyebrow">— Before you write —</div>
          <h3 class="section-head">A few honest answers, <em>so the email is shorter.</em></h3>
          <div class="faq">
            <div class="faq-row">
              <div class="q">What roles are you considering?</div>
              <div class="a">
                Head of Design, VP Design, Chief Design Officer. <em>The senior leadership tier.</em>
                I am not considering individual-contributor roles, design-management roles below the
                Director title, or contract work outside Precocity's existing book.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-row">
              <div class="q">Where will you work?</div>
              <div class="a">
                Dallas (where I live), New York, the Bay Area, Seattle, or fully remote. I will
                relocate for the right role. I will not relocate for a fast-growth startup whose
                runway is the recruiter's main selling point.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-row">
              <div class="q">What companies are interesting?</div>
              <div class="a">
                Companies where design has earned a real seat and the CEO can name three things
                their best designer shipped last quarter. I'm specifically interested in flagship
                consumer and tooling companies — LEGO, Netflix, Apple, Airbnb, and the equivalents.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-row">
              <div class="q">Will you do a take-home?</div>
              <div class="a">
                <em>No.</em> The work on this site is the take-home. I will do a paid, time-boxed
                advisory engagement at any stage of the process if it helps both sides decide.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-row">
              <div class="q">Are you doing speaking, writing, advising on the side?</div>
              <div class="a">
                Speaking, occasionally and selectively. Writing, only here. Advisory, only by
                introduction. I am not signing on as a podcast guest unless you've read the work.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section note">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="marker">§ 04</div>
        <div>
          <div class="section-eyebrow">— A note on response —</div>
          <p>
            I read every email that arrives at this address. I reply inside two business days,
            including the ones I'm declining — declining is also a response. If you do not hear
            back inside a week, the email did not arrive; resend.
          </p>
          <div class="stamp">— Last revised Q1 2026 · Updated quarterly —</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
